race.comment: HIS LADY BAY (7) peaks and didn't have the best of it placing as a $2.6F at Warrnambool last time. Showed enough in town and the back of her first preparation to suggest she can make amends. MISSY AGGRAVATION (10) jumped out well and resumed with a solid effort at Mornington after a slow start. The step-up in trip is sure to suit and the 1.5kg apprentice will give her every hope from an inside barrier. PEACE SEEKER (12) disappointed at Stawell but the Mornington effort prior was promising. Maps for a soft run and she should also enjoy the longer journey. PRINCESS PAINTON (2) resumes and has three jumpouts under the saddle. Expect her to be improved and ready to go over the 1525m. The race day betting should tell plenty.
